The teachers have their contact information in your students work. Also please do not send back the text books or reading books they are needed for work....as well as incomplete work. If your student needs help or has questions it's better to contact the teacher instead of sending back incomplete assignments.

post_text:
The Oelrichs School District will be having a special honoring assembly for K-12 on Friday January 31st. 2020 at 2:30 in the gymnasium.
We will recognize and honor student achievement from the past semester including Honor Roll (3.5 gpa-B+) and Exceptional Honors for students in Middle School and High School who maintained a 4.0 gpa for the semester. There will be honors fro all students k-12!
The Oelrichs School family wants to recognize achievements for our students and share those achievements with family and friends.
All are welcome to attend. Lemonade and cookies will be served.
As always, we want to thank our students' parents,grandparents and all their family members for sharing your students with us at Oelrichs and encouraging them to be part of the Oelrich's family!

What: Honoring Assembly
When:Jan 31,2020 Friday at 2:30pm
Where:Oelrichs School Gymnasium

post_text:
The Oelrichs School Student Council is presenting a School/Community wide RED RIBBON Halloween Carnival. It will take place on Wednesday, October 30, 2019. We plan to start at 2:30 pm and then provide an activity bus for students who need transportation at 5:15. There will be a scary movie, games, activities, a haunted room and a cake walk. Please see the flyer below for more information. We hope all our students will be able to attend as well as family and community.
A permission slip for this afterschool activity and activity bus is being sent home with students this week. It must be returned by Thursday! Students who do not have a permission slip will not be allowed to stay and will be transporting home on the regular bus after school. If you plan to attend and transport your student, please mark that appropriate box on the permission slip and return it to the school by Thursday.
It will be a fun time for all!! Wear Red to show support for Red Ribbon week and being drug and alcohol free!!
